quran[21]{c,v,t}:
  16,30,"And ňĻwhenňļ it is said to those mindful ňĻof Allahňļ, ‚ÄúWhat has your Lord revealed?‚ÄĚ They say, ‚ÄúAll the best!‚ÄĚ For those who do good in this world, there is goodness. But far better is the ňĻeternalňļ Home of the Hereafter. How excellent indeed is the home of the righteous"
  16,31,"the Gardens of Eternity which they will enter, under which rivers flow. In it they will have whatever they desire. This is how Allah rewards the righteous‚ÄĒ"
  16,32,"those whose souls the angels take while they are virtuous, saying ňĻto themňļ, ‚ÄúPeace be upon you! Enter Paradise for what you used to do.‚ÄĚ"
  16,33,"Are they only awaiting the coming of the angels or the command of your Lord ňĻO Prophetňļ? So were those before them. And Allah never wronged them, but it was they who wronged themselves"
  16,34,"Then the evil ňĻconsequencesňļ of their deeds overtook them, and they were overwhelmed by what they used to ridicule"
  16,35,"The polytheists argue, ‚ÄúHad Allah willed, neither we nor our forefathers would have worshipped anything other than Him, nor prohibited anything without His command.‚ÄĚ So did those before them. Is not the messengers‚Äô duty only to deliver ňĻthe messageňļ clearly"
  16,36,"We surely sent a messenger to every community, saying, ‚ÄúWorship Allah and shun false gods.‚ÄĚ But some of them were guided by Allah, while others were destined to stray. So travel throughout the land and see the fate of the deniers"
  16,37,"Even though you ňĻO Prophetňļ are keen on their guidance, Allah certainly does not guide those He leaves to stray, and they will have no helpers"
  16,38,"They swear by Allah their most solemn oaths that Allah will never raise the dead to life. Yes ňĻHe willňļ! It is a true promise binding on Him, but most people do not know"
  16,39,"ňĻHe will do thatňļ to make clear to them what they disagreed on, and for the disbelievers to know that they were liars"
  16,40,"If We ever will something ňĻto existňļ, all We say is: ‚ÄúBe!‚ÄĚ And it is"
  16,41,"As for those who emigrated in ňĻthe cause ofňļ Allah after being persecuted, We will surely bless them with a good home in this world. But the reward of the Hereafter is far better, if only they knew"
  16,42,"ňĻIt isňļ they who have patiently endured, and in their Lord they put their trust"
  16,43,"We did not send ňĻmessengersňļ before you ňĻO Prophetňļ except mere men inspired by Us. If you ňĻpolytheistsňļ do not know ňĻthis alreadyňļ, then ask those who have knowledge ňĻof the Scripturesňļ"
  16,44,"ňĻWe sent themňļ with clear proofs and divine Books. And We have sent down to you ňĻO Prophetňļ the Reminder, so that you may explain to people what has been revealed for them, and perhaps they will reflect"
  16,45,Do those who devise evil plots feel secure that Allah will not cause the earth to swallow them? Or that the torment will not come upon them in ways they cannot comprehend
  16,46,"Or that He will not seize them while they go about ňĻtheir dayňļ, for then they will have no escape"
  16,47,"Or that He will not destroy them gradually? But your Lord is truly Ever Gracious, Most Merciful"
  16,48,"Have they not considered how the shadows of everything Allah has created incline to the right and the left ňĻas the sun movesňļ, totally submitting to Allah in all humility"
  16,49,"And to Allah ňĻaloneňļ bows down ňĻin submissionňļ¬†whatever is in the heavens and whatever is on the earth of living creatures, as do the angels‚ÄĒwho are not too proud ňĻto do soňļ"
  16,50,"They¬†fear their Lord above them, and do whatever they are commanded"